guide: Â§7Carrots and potatoes from killing
Â§7Zombies in graveyard do count.
Â§7Use /warp trapper to accept a quest
Â§7and use SkyHanni's Trapper features
Â§7to make this easier. Bring a bow with you.
Â§7Mine Diamonds in the Mines of Divan
Â§7(HotM 3) or in the carts in the Dwarven Mines.

Â§7Diamond Spreadings in your Minions if you want.
Â§7Wear armor enchanted with Growth 5

Â§7progress in the Community Goal.
Â§7Optimal tool:
Â§7Golden Axe with Efficiency 5

Â§7Get Haste 3 from a splash to instamine wood

Â§7Place as many minions as you can
Â§7give them a medium storage and the best fuel

Â§7while going for other grinds.
Â§7Â§lMake sure to always have a pet active!
Â§7Use a Silk Touch and Efficiency Golden Axe and

Â§7Optimal tool:
Â§7Golden Axe with Efficiency 5
Â§7Reforges: Double-Bit or Lush
Â§7Get Haste 3 from a splash to instamine wood

Â§7Get Enchanting Level 10 and play

21.description: Â§7Equip an Uncommon or higher tiered Rock Pet
guide: Â§7You get the Rock Pet from mining ores.
Â§7The Common Rock unlocks at 2.5k broken ores,
Â§7the Uncommon one at 7.5k. You can also upgrade
Â§7your common rock at Kat but this will take a day.
Â§7Farm in the Garden. Remember Crop Milestones
Â§7grant a lot of XP. Carrots can also benefit this
Â§7as you can use pet candies made out of them to
Â§7contribute to another goal.
Â§7Fish in The Park and make sure rain is active.
Â§7Do not stand/have your bobber under solid blocks
Â§7as this will slow your speed down by a lot.
Â§7You will get this passively by leveling up
Â§7skills, if you don't forget to put the money
Â§7in your bank ;-)
Â§7Craft some easy minions while also getting
Â§7those that will help with this Bingo.
Â§7You might wanna go further than that to
Â§7help with other goals.
Â§7Craft Leather, Iron, Gold and Diamond Armor
Â§7Collect Ender Armor from The End (8 pieces including equipment)
Â§7Craft Leaflet, Farm Suit, Mushroom and Cactus Armor
Â§7Buy Squire, Rosetta's, Celeste and Starlight Armor from Rosetta
Â§7You will unlock this while going
Â§7for Mushroom Collector.
Â§7Remember to get the Glowstone Dust
Â§7by buying a Glowstone from The Builder
Â§7and breaking it on your island.
Â§7Going for the Slayer Goal will give you
Â§7quite some progress here if you do it
Â§7on your own with Revenant Bosses.
Â§7Reforge your Void Sword to Sharp
Â§7at the Blacksmith in the Hub (-28 69 -125),
Â§7or enchant any weapon with Critical 5 (costs 50 Levels).
Â§7You might also get it from receiving a Splash.
Â§7Kill Cows in The Barn to unlock this
Â§7and craft it using the materials you
Â§7got along the way.
Â§7Follow the Lone Adventurers quest in The End
Â§7until you get the Bow.
Â§7Apply it to an armor piece using the Blacksmith.
Â§7This can take quite some time and money
Â§7as it is RNG based.
Â§7To help with this, try to make bigger crafts
Â§7by hand for Carpentry levels. Don't forget
Â§7to do some Alchemy with Materials gathered from the Garden.
Â§7Also do your daily experiments and make sure
Â§7to have a pet active at all times
Â§7(any pet works, even level 100).
Â§7Do your daily commissions in the Dwarven Mines
Â§7(and Crystal Hollows). Also participate in any
Â§7active event there that you come across.
Â§7Collect Superboom TNT from dungeons
Â§7or buy some from Ophelia in The Dungeon Hub.
Â§7Then use them on the crypts you run
Â§7across inside a dungeon.

3.description: Â§7Obtain a Bronze Medal in a Farming Contest
guide: Â§7You need Farming Level 10 for this.
Â§7Your best options will most likely be
Â§7potato contests as you need a lot of
Â§7potatoes for a different goal or mushroom
Â§7contests with a silk touch gold axe.
Â§7Open chests in the Crystal Hollows (Heart of the Mountain III),
Â§7do commissions in The Dwarven Mines,
Â§7claim your daily powder from the Puzzler and
Â§7from giving Fetchur the items he asks for.
Â§7Fetchurs items are all listed in the Wiki.
Â§7Try to do those while a '2x Powder' event is active.
Â§7Buy a Dirt Bottle (100k) from the
Â§7Smithmonger in the Hub and reforge
Â§7an uncommon or higher rarity weapon with it.
Â§7You will most likely get this from
Â§7leveling up skills.
Â§7If that isnt enough, kill Endermen and
Â§7mine nodes in The End to get money.
Â§7Remember to actually put the money
Â§7you get in the Bank :)
Â§7Collect those you run along while doing other goals.
Â§7If you have trouble check TimeDeo's fairy soul
Â§7 tutorial on YouTube or use /neusouls on/off
Â§7to get waypoints.
Â§7Kill the Goblins you can find in the
Â§7Dwarven Mines and Crystal Hollows.
Â§7You will need Mining 12 for this.
Â§7This requires Catacombs Level 3 and
Â§7a completion of the 2 floors before.
Â§7You may need help from party finder
Â§7or friends for this.
Â§7You will get this passively while going
Â§7for other grinds as you need Combat 15 for
Â§7the dungeon task. Dont forget to claim
Â§7your bestiary rewards as you unlock them.
Â§7Talk to Jamie in the Hub and
Â§7claim the Rogue Sword from him.
Â§7Right click it to gain +100 Speed.
Â§7Or just wait for a splash.
Â§7Kill Spiders in the Spider's Den (/warp spider)
Â§7place a few Spider Minions and participate
Â§7in killing Arachne in Arachne's Sanctuary.
Â§7Recommended to wear a Cow Head to avoid the poison.
Â§7Dont forget to fuel your minions and give them
Â§7a storage. Also collect them in time.
Â§7You need a score of 230 or higher
Â§7in Floor 1 or higher to get this.
Â§7Opening will cost 100k coins.
Â§7You will most likely gain passive
Â§7progress in here. Use the best pickaxe
Â§7you can get your hands on and mine.
Â§7Craft Leather, Iron, Gold and Diamond Armor
Â§7Collect Ender Armor from The End (8 pieces including equipment)
Â§7Craft Leaflet, Farm Suit, Mushroom and Cactus Armor
Â§7Buy Squire, Rosetta's, Celeste and Starlight Armor from Rosetta
Â§7Obtained from completing any race with 4/4
Â§7at Guildford in the Dungeon Hub.

29.description: Â§7Equip an Uncommon or higher tiered Rock Pet
guide: Â§7You get the Rock Pet from mining ores.
Â§7The Common Rock unlocks at 2.5k broken ores,
Â§7the Uncommon one at 7.5k. You can also upgrade
Â§7your common rock at Kat but this will take a day.
Â§7To help with this, try to make bigger crafts
Â§7by hand for Carpentry levels. Don't forget
Â§7to do some Alchemy with Materials gathered from the Garden.
Â§7Also do your daily experiments and make sure
Â§7to have a pet active at all times
Â§7(any pet works, even level 100).
Â§7Wear Mushroom Armor enchanted with Growth 5
Â§7during the night.
Â§7Growth 5 requires Enchanting Level 5
Â§7and costs 50 Experience Levels per piece.
Â§7Farm crops mainly in The Garden
Â§7as they help progressing with
Â§7the XP from Crop Milestones.
Â§7You will need 50k potato collection
Â§7and 160 enchanted potatoes for this.
Â§7You might want to utilize The Garden for this.
Â§7Kill Cows in The Barn to unlock this
Â§7and craft it using the materials you
Â§7got along the way.

39.description: Â§7Consume a Mushed Glowy Tonic Potion
guide: Â§7Follow Moby's quest in the desert
Â§7until you unlock the shop.
Â§7Then you need 8 full Chum Buckets and
Â§710 Glowing Mushrooms to buy it from Moby.
Â§7Kill goblins or open loot chests in the Crystal Hollows,
Â§7then just throw them until you get a Golden Goblin.
Â§7Higher level eggs have higher chances of spawning, but are also rarer.
Â§7You can also spawn it from mining ores in the Dwarven Mines.
Â§7Â§lNo eggs:
Â§7Bingo, Enderman, Grandma Wolf, Armadillo, Squid,
Â§7Guardian, Bee, Dolphin, Reindeer, Rock, Tarantula,
Â§7Owl and Zoo.
Â§7Â§lEggs:
Â§7Jerry, Silverfish, Pig, Rabbit, Endermite and Bat.
Â§7If you use eggs, you will need 2.5k Raw Chicken Collection
Â§7and a lot of eggs.
Â§7Use /warp trapper to accept a quest
Â§7and use SkyHanni's Trapper features
Â§7to make this easier. Bring a bow with you.
Â§7Use the best rod you can get
Â§7your hands on (Chum Rod is a good option),
Â§7enchant it and don't forget to use baits.
Â§7You might also want to use Angler Armor.
Â§7Do 3 Tier 1 Revenant Horror Bosses
Â§7and claim the rewards by talking to Maddox.
Â§7Doing this will bring you decently close
Â§7to your 10th Minion Slot which will be
Â§7useful for other goals. Craft all the
Â§7Minions you get across. Remember that
Â§7you can buy material from a few NPCs.
Â§7Craft Leather, Iron, Gold and Diamond Armor
Â§7and equip them all in one lobby.
Â§7You will get decent progress towards this
Â§7while going for other grinds. You will most
Â§7likely have to kill some Enderman in The End
Â§7to finish this. Don't forget to claim your
Â§7bestiary rewards.
Â§7Kill Cows in The Barn to unlock this
Â§7and craft it using the materials you
Â§7got along the way.
Â§7Carrots and potatoes from killing
Â§7Zombies in graveyard do count.
Â§7This requires Catacombs Level 1 and
Â§7a completion of the previous floor.
Â§7You may need help from party finder
Â§7or friends for this.
Â§7You can unlock 17/17 Farming Collections,
Â§76/11 Combat Collections, 6/6 Foraging Collections,
Â§714/22 Mining Collections for a total of 43 collections.
Â§7You will also get some Fishing Collections.
Â§7You will need Heart of the Mountain 3
Â§7for this (this can be done by doing
Â§74 commissions a day for 3 days). In the
Â§7Crystal Hollows you will need to find
Â§7Mines of Divan and 4 different tools in there.
Â§7You will need Heart of the Mountain 3
Â§7for this (this can be done by doing
Â§74 commissions a day for 3 days). Aim to
Â§7use 10 or more Minions for this and give
Â§7them the best fuel and storage you have
Â§7access to. Collect in time!
Â§7Get yourself a splash, equip a Bingo Pet
Â§7and get the cake buff by eating the cakes
Â§7on owocato's, xMeru's or prtl's island.
Â§7If this doesn't finish it, get a Void Sword (200k) in the End
Â§7and hold it while some Ender Armor and/or Equipment.
Â§7You might want to go for Sugar Cane
Â§7in your Garden, but you can also use
Â§7the wheat in The Hub.
Â§7Talk to Jamie in the Hub and
Â§7claim the Rogue Sword from him.
Â§7Right click it to gain +100 Speed.
Â§7Or just wait for a splash.

24.description: Â§7Find 1 pair in the Experimentation Table
guide: Â§7Get Enchanting Level 10 and play
Â§7the first tier in the Experimentation Table.
Â§7List of more than 12 talismans:
Â§7Buy all 6 Talismans for 26k from the Adventurer in The Hub
Â§7Collection Talismans:
Â§7Night Vision Charm, Farming Talisman, Vaccine Talisman,
Â§7Gravity Talisman, Talisman of Coins, Magnetic Talisman,
Â§7Emerald Ring, Wood Affinity Talisman, Speed Talisman,
Â§7Potion Affinity Talisman
Â§7Other:
Â§7Archaeologists Compass, Shiny Yellow Rock, King Talisman,
Â§7Campfire Initiate Badge, Cat Talisman, Spider Talisman.
Â§7Don't forget to take the 4 Bonus accessory bag slots from
Â§7the Redstone Miner, he needs 1920 Redstone in total.
Â§7To get the required Gold Medal you'll have
Â§7to either trade in 4 Silver or 8 Bronze Medals
Â§7with Anita. The crops recommended for this are:
Â§7Wheat, Carrot, Potato, Cactus, and Mushroom.
Â§7Buy a Dirt Bottle (100k) from Smithmonger in the Hub

Â§7Make sure to NOT shift-click it out
Â§7of the menu after applying!
Â§7For this you can kill Arachne in the Spider's Den,
Â§7salvage the gear drops you get from that

Â§7secret chests in dungeons.
Â§7Claim your cake buff (visit skyerzz, xMeru or prtl)
Â§7hold an Angler 4 or 5 rod and visit someone

Â§7Open chests in the Crystal Hollows (Heart of the Mountain III),
Â§7do commissions in The Dwarven Mines,
Â§7claim your daily powder from the Puzzler and
Â§7from giving Fetchur the items he asks for.
Â§7Fetchurs items are all listed in the Wiki.
Â§7Try to do those while a '2x Powder' event is active.
Â§7You will most likely get this from
Â§7leveling up skills.
Â§7Remember to actually put the money
Â§7you get in the Bank :)
Â§7Use a Chicken Head to get enough eggs
Â§7to craft an Enchanted Egg (2.5k Chicken Collection).

Â§7craft a Jerry pet.

Â§7Wheat, Mushroom or Cobblestone.
Â§7The first 2 options will require 75 pelts
Â§7to get to t12. Use /warp trapper and SkyHanni's

Â§7You will get passive progress for this
Â§7while going for other goals. If you want
Â§7to specifically go for this, use a
Â§7Cobblestone Generator on your island.
Â§7You will passively get progress
Â§7in this by just having a pet
Â§7equipped all time. Even a
Â§7Level 100 pet works for this.
Â§7Use Enchanted Sugar that you get from
Â§7killing pests in The Garden or from
Â§7farming some Sugar Cane to brew
Â§7Speed Potions (you will also need
Â§7some nether warts for Awkward Potions first)
Â§7Mine 50 Iron in the Gold Mine
Â§7to unlock Iron Minions. Then buy
Â§7Iron from the Mine Merchant in The Hub

Â§7craft as many minions as you can.

Â§7have access to and don't forget Auto Smelters.

Â§7To help with this, try to make bigger crafts
Â§7by hand for Carpentry levels.
Â§7Also do your daily experiments and make sure
Â§7to have a pet active at all times
Â§7(any pet works, even level 100).
Â§7Save your coins from Meiser and ideally
Â§7you get a score of 270+ in your run for
Â§7High Score! You may need more coins than
Â§7250k if you do drop rarer loot.
Â§7Remember you can open chests at Croesus
Â§7in the Dungeon Hub up to 48h after the run.
Â§7Get yourself a splash, equip a Bingo Pet
Â§7and get the cake buff by eating the cakes
Â§7on owocato's, xMeru's or prtl's island.
Â§7If this doesn't finish it, get a Void Sword (200k) in the End
Â§7and hold it while some Ender Armor and/or Equipment.
Â§7You will get passive progress for this
Â§7while going for other goals. If you want
Â§7to specifically go for this, use a
Â§7Cobblestone Generator on your island.
Â§7Unlock Skeleton Minions by killing skeletons you
Â§7run into along your way. Then buy
Â§7Bones from the Adventurer in The Hub
Â§7and craft as many minions as you can.
Â§7Give them the best fuel and storage you
Â§7have access to.
Â§7Remember to collect in time.
Â§7You will most likely get this from
Â§7leveling up skills.
Â§7Remember to actually put the money
Â§7you get in the Bank :)
Â§7Wear armor enchanted with Growth 5
Â§7(Enchanting Level 5), preferably Ender Armor

Â§7during the night.
Â§7Applying Growth 5 costs 50 Levels each.
Â§7If you still struggle, reforge your
Â§7armor to Titanic.

Â§7Place as many minions as you can,

Â§7Â§nEggs:Â§r

Â§7You can unlock 17/17 Farming Collections,

Â§714/22 Mining Collections for a total of 43 collections.
Â§7You will also get some Fishing Collections.
Â§7Carrots and potatoes from killing

Â§7Reforge your Void Sword to Sharp

Â§7one Chicken Minion to generate more of those over time.

42.description: Â§7Gain coins from the Scavenger Enchantment
guide: Â§7Kill mobs with a weapon that you have
Â§7Scavenger 3+ applied to.
Â§7Use the best rod you can get
Â§7your hands on (Chum Rod is a good option),
Â§7enchant it and don't forget to use baits.
Â§7You might also want to use Angler Armor.
Â§7Do 3 Tier 1 Revenant Horror Bosses
Â§7and claim the rewards by talking to Maddox.
Â§7Doing this will bring you decently close
Â§7to your 10th Minion Slot which will be
Â§7useful for other goals. Craft all the
Â§7Minions you get across. Remember that
Â§7you can buy material from a few NPCs.
Â§7Craft Leather, Iron, Gold and Diamond Armor
Â§7and equip them all in one lobby.
Â§7You will get decent progress towards this
Â§7while going for other grinds. You will most
Â§7likely have to kill some Enderman in The End
Â§7to finish this. Don't forget to claim your
Â§7bestiary rewards.
Â§7Kill Cows in The Barn to unlock this
Â§7and craft it using the materials you
Â§7got along the way.
Â§7Carrots and potatoes from killing
Â§7Zombies in graveyard do count.
Â§7This requires Catacombs Level 1 and
Â§7a completion of the previous floor.
Â§7You may need help from party finder
Â§7or friends for this.
Â§7You can unlock 17/17 Farming Collections,
Â§76/11 Combat Collections, 6/6 Foraging Collections,
Â§714/22 Mining Collections for a total of 43 collections.
Â§7You will also get some Fishing Collections.
Â§7You will need Heart of the Mountain 3
Â§7for this (this can be done by doing
Â§74 commissions a day for 3 days). In the
Â§7Crystal Hollows you will need to find
Â§7Mines of Divan and 4 different tools in there.
Â§7You will need Heart of the Mountain 3
Â§7for this (this can be done by doing
Â§74 commissions a day for 3 days). Aim to
Â§7use 10 or more Minions for this and give
Â§7them the best fuel and storage you have
Â§7access to. Collect in time!
Â§7Get yourself a splash, equip a Bingo Pet
Â§7and get the cake buff by eating the cakes
Â§7on owocato's, xMeru's or prtl's island.
Â§7If this doesn't finish it, get a Void Sword (200k) in the End
Â§7and hold it while some Ender Armor and/or Equipment.
Â§7You might want to go for Sugar Cane
Â§7in your Garden, but you can also use
Â§7the wheat in The Hub.
Â§7Talk to Jamie in the Hub and
Â§7claim the Rogue Sword from him.
Â§7Right click it to gain +100 Speed.
Â§7Or just wait for a splash.

24.description: Â§7Find 1 pair in the Experimentation Table
guide: Â§7Get Enchanting Level 10 and play
Â§7the first tier in the Experimentation Table.
Â§7List of more than 12 talismans:
Â§7Buy all 6 Talismans for 26k from the Adventurer in The Hub
Â§7Collection Talismans:
Â§7Night Vision Charm, Farming Talisman, Vaccine Talisman,
Â§7Gravity Talisman, Talisman of Coins, Magnetic Talisman,
Â§7Emerald Ring, Wood Affinity Talisman, Speed Talisman,
Â§7Potion Affinity Talisman
Â§7Other:
Â§7Archaeologists Compass, Shiny Yellow Rock, King Talisman,
Â§7Campfire Initiate Badge, Cat Talisman, Spider Talisman.
Â§7Don't forget to take the 4 Bonus accessory bag slots from
Â§7the Redstone Miner, he needs 1920 Redstone in total.
Â§7To get the required Gold Medal you'll have
Â§7to either trade in 4 Silver or 8 Bronze Medals
Â§7with Anita. The crops recommended for this are:
Â§7Wheat, Carrot, Potato, Cactus, and Mushroom.
Â§7Buy a Dirt Bottle (100k) from Smithmonger in the Hub
Â§7and reforge a weapon with it.
Â§7Make sure to NOT shift-click it out
Â§7of the menu after applying!
Â§7For this you can kill Arachne in the Spider's Den,
Â§7salvage the gear drops you get from that
Â§7 and also gain Spider Essence from opening
Â§7secret chests in dungeons.
Â§7Claim your cake buff (visit skyerzz, xMeru or prtl)
Â§7hold an Angler 4 or 5 rod and visit someone
Â§7with a Sea Creature Chance beacon.
Â§7Open chests in the Crystal Hollows (Heart of the Mountain III),
Â§7do commissions in The Dwarven Mines,
Â§7claim your daily powder from the Puzzler and
Â§7from giving Fetchur the items he asks for.
Â§7Fetchurs items are all listed in the Wiki.
Â§7Try to do those while a '2x Powder' event is active.
Â§7You will most likely get this from
Â§7leveling up skills.
Â§7Remember to actually put the money
Â§7you get in the Bank :)
Â§7Use a Chicken Head to get enough eggs
Â§7to craft an Enchanted Egg (2.5k Chicken Collection).
Â§7With your Enchanted Egg and 8 Move Jerry's,
Â§7craft a Jerry pet.
Â§7For this you either want to go for
Â§7Wheat, Mushroom or Cobblestone.
Â§7The first 2 options will require 75 pelts
Â§7to get to t12. Use /warp trapper and SkyHanni's
Â§7Trapper Features to help with that.
Â§7You will get passive progress for this
Â§7while going for other goals. If you want
Â§7to specifically go for this, use a
Â§7Cobblestone Generator on your island.
Â§7You will passively get progress
Â§7in this by just having a pet
Â§7equipped all time. Even a
Â§7Level 100 pet works for this.
Â§7Use Enchanted Sugar that you get from
Â§7killing pests in The Garden or from
Â§7farming some Sugar Cane to brew
Â§7Speed Potions (you will also need
Â§7some nether warts for Awkward Potions first)
Â§7Mine 50 Iron in the Gold Mine
Â§7to unlock Iron Minions. Then buy
Â§7Iron from the Mine Merchant in The Hub
Â§7and Iron Forger in the Gold Mine and
Â§7craft as many minions as you can.
Â§7Give them the best fuel and storage you
Â§7have access to and don't forget Auto Smelters.
Â§7Remember to collect in time.
Â§7To help with this, try to make bigger crafts
Â§7by hand for Carpentry levels.
Â§7Also do your daily experiments and make sure
Â§7to have a pet active at all times
Â§7(any pet works, even level 100).
Â§7Save your coins from Meiser and ideally
Â§7you get a score of 270+ in your run for
Â§7High Score! You may need more coins than
Â§7250k if you do drop rarer loot.
Â§7Remember you can open chests at Croesus
Â§7in the Dungeon Hub up to 48h after the run.
Â§7Get yourself a splash, equip a Bingo Pet
Â§7and get the cake buff by eating the cakes
Â§7on owocato's, xMeru's or prtl's island.
Â§7If this doesn't finish it, get a Void Sword (200k) in the End
Â§7and hold it while some Ender Armor and/or Equipment.
Â§7You will get passive progress for this
Â§7while going for other goals. If you want
Â§7to specifically go for this, use a
Â§7Cobblestone Generator on your island.
Â§7Unlock Skeleton Minions by killing skeletons you
Â§7run into along your way. Then buy
Â§7Bones from the Adventurer in The Hub
Â§7and craft as many minions as you can.
Â§7Give them the best fuel and storage you
Â§7have access to.
Â§7Remember to collect in time.
Â§7You will most likely get this from
Â§7leveling up skills.
Â§7Remember to actually put the money
Â§7you get in the Bank :)
Â§7Wear armor enchanted with Growth 5
Â§7(Enchanting Level 5), preferably Ender Armor
Â§7while you're in The End or Mushroom Armor
Â§7during the night.
Â§7Applying Growth 5 costs 50 Levels each.
Â§7If you still struggle, reforge your
Â§7armor to Titanic.

20.description: Â§7Wear a full set of Glacite
guide: Â§7You will need Mining 12 for this as you
Â§7need to enter the Dwarven Mines for this.
Â§7Remember that Glacite Walkers take more
Â§7damage from pickaxes.
Â§7This requires Catacombs Level 1 and
Â§7a completion of the previous floor.
Â§7You may need help from party finder
Â§7or friends for this.
Â§7To get easy progress in this do
Â§7contests like Wheat, Potato, Carrot
Â§7or Mushroom as those are easy
Â§7Bronze or Silver Medals to get.
Â§7Optimal tool:
Â§7Golden Axe with Efficiency 5
Â§7Reforges: Double-Bit or Lush
Â§7Get Haste 3 from a splash to instamine wood
Â§7Forage in the Hub.
Â§7Place as many minions as you can,
Â§7give them a medium storage and the best fuel
Â§7you can. Collect them in time.

24.description: Â§7Get Bronze or higher in a contest
guide: Â§7For this you will need Farming 10.
Â§7Your best options for this will probably be
Â§7Wheat/Potato/Carrot in the Garden or Mushroom
Â§7if you use an Efficiency 5 Silk Touch Gold Axe
Â§7in the Desert.
Â§7Buy a Dirt Bottle (100k) from the Smithmonger
Â§7in the Hub and reforge a weapon with it.
Â§7Â§4Make sure to NOT shift-click it out
Â§7Â§4of the menu after applying!
Â§7You will get some progress for this
Â§7by working on other goals.
Â§7The easiest to go for are:
Â§7Mushroom, Oak Wood, Bone,
Â§7Sand, Wheat, Iron and Seeds.
Â§7Reforge your Void Sword to Sharp
Â§7at the Blacksmith in the Hub,
Â§7or enchant any weapon with Critical 5
Â§7(costs 50 Levels).
Â§7For this you will need Combat 15 and
Â§7completion of the previous floor.
Â§7Going for this with your friends is
Â§7probably the best option or you
Â§7could use party finder.
Â§7Get the common Rock from mining
Â§72.5k Ores and hand it to Kat in The Hub
Â§7(takes a day and 100k coins) or mine
Â§75k more Ores to get the uncommon Rock.
Â§7Remember to equip it!
Â§7Craft Leather, Iron, Gold, Diamond, Mushroom
Â§7and Leaflet Armor. Grind Glacite Armor
Â§7for the goal I've got Chills!
Â§7and equip them all in one lobby.
Â§7Hit 10 Endermen in The End
Â§7so they follow you, then kill them
Â§7all as quickly as you can.
Â§7You most likely want to use Ender Armor
Â§7and a Void Sword for this.
Â§7Do 3 Tier 1 Revenant Horror Bosses
Â§7and claim the rewards by talking to Maddox.
Â§7Â§nNo eggs:Â§r
Â§7Bingo, Endermen, Grandma Wolf, Armadillo,
Â§7Squid, Guardian, Bee, Dolphin, Reindeer,
Â§7Rock, Tarantula, Owl and Zoo
Â§7Â§nEggs:Â§r
Â§7Jerry, Silverfish, Pig, Rabbit, Endermite and Bat
Â§7If you do eggs you will need 2.5k Chicken Collection
Â§7and you'll want a Chicken Minion that can create more
Â§7Enchanted Eggs for you once you put your first one in.
Â§7Once you acquire a Void Sword and a decent
Â§7armor like Ender or Glacite this should be
Â§7fairly easy to do. You might get a little
Â§7progress in this from doing the Slayer Goal.
